This paper deals with information extraction, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of reinforcement learning (RL) to improve extraction accuracy suggests that this paper could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves search queries and reconciliation of extracted values, which are tasks related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB).
